description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Work 18 hours over three days as a Dietician at the Cotswold Spa in Worchester where you will be valued and supported as you help people build a brighter future.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You’ll join the team caring for young people and adults in this specialist inpatient and day-patient eating disorder service.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;As a Dietician, you will manage a clinical caseload where you will provide dietetic assessment, diagnosis, treatment programmes to individual service users and will be requested to design and deliver training.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will provide advice, guidance and information to your peers, service users and their family as you support them through their recovery journey, including menu planning with the catering department and education workshops.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Working as part of a multidisciplinary team, you will be supported regionally and will have access to a variety of training and online courses to support your career development and growth.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Implement dietetic audits.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Contribute to the Nutrition Steering Group.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Implementation and planning of individual dietary treatment plans.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Facilitate the safe discharge of service users with nutritional and dietetic plans.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;To be successful in this role, you&#39;ll need:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Qualification in Dietetics and registration with HCPC and BDA.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Experience with Eating Disorders&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Experience within a similar environment&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you will get:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Annual salary of £15,247.44&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;The equivalent of 33 days annual leave – plus your birthday off!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Free meals and parking&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Wellbeing support and activities&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Career development and training&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Pension contribution&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Life Assurance&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Enhanced Maternity Package&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;There is also a range of other benefits including retail discounts and special offers, car leasing without a credit check, holiday financing and much more.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About your next employer:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will be working for an established, stable and agile company with a unique approach to the delivery of care. With a network of over 70 services across England and Wales, providing four services including: Mental Health, Neurological, Learning Disabilities &amp; Autism, Children &amp; Education, there is an opportunity for you to grow and move with Elysium.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span&gt;Elysium Healthcare follows safer recruitment of staff for all appointments. It is a requirement that all staff understand it is each person’s individual responsibility and are committed to promoting and safeguarding the welfare of service users. Candidates will be subject to an Enhanced DBS disclosure.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
